Returns: true if the argument type has a plural style part sequence and semantics, for example @B_android#icu#text#MessagePattern#ArgType#PLURAL_E@ and @B_android#icu#text#MessagePattern#ArgType#SELECTORDINAL_E@.

ClassDesc: Argument type constants. Returned by Part.getArgType() for ARG_START and ARG_LIMIT parts. Messages nested inside an argument are each delimited by MSG_START and MSG_LIMIT, with a nesting level one greater than the surrounding message.
